
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Faq";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}


<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>FAQ</title>


    <link href="@Url.Content("~/Styles/bootstrap.min.css")" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    <script src="~/Scripts/jquery-3.4.1.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
    <script src="~/Scripts/bootstrap.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
    <style>
        .collapsible {
            background-color: cornflowerblue;
            color: black;
            cursor: pointer;
            padding: 18px;
            width: 100%;
            border: none;
            text-align: left;
            outline: none;
            font-size: 15px;
        }

            .active, .collapsible:hover {
                background-color: lightgrey;
            }

        .content {
            padding: 0 18px;
            display: none;
            overflow: hidden;
            background-color: white;
        }
    </style>

</head>
<body>
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <p>Find Answers and general information in our FAQ section</p>

    <button type="button" class="collapsible">Accessibility</button>
    <div class="content">
        <p>Every Community Transit bus is equipped with a wheelchair lift or ramp. Our Coach operators are trained to assist disabled passengers with boarding and securing their mobility device.</p>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="collapsible">Animals on Buses</button>
    <div class="content">
        <p>We appreciate animals and pets in all shapes and sizes, so we have policies in place to ensure the safety of service and non-service animals when it comes to riding our buses.</p>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="collapsible">Fare Policy</button>
    <div class="content">
        <p>Community Transit collects fares on all trips. </p>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="collapsible">Rules and Policies</button>
    <div class="content">
        <p>Bus conduct is regulated by state laws and Community Transit policies to make the ride safe and enjoyable for all passengers.</p>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="collapsible">Safety and Security</button>
    <div class="content">
        <p>Community Transit contracts with the Snohomish County Sheriff's Department to provide safety and security for our buses and park & rides. All buses have two-way radios and alarm systems to notify our dispatchers if there is a problem or need for assistance. We also have security cameras on board buses and at some park & rides.</p>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="collapsible">Bikes</button>
    <div class="content">
        <p>Every Community Transit bus is equipped with a front rack that holds at least two bicycles. Some buses now have three-bike racks, and more will be installed later in 2008. Simple instructions for use are printed on the bike rack.</p>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="collapsible">Lost and Found</button>
    <div class="content">
        <p>If you lose an item on the bus, call the Community Transit RideStore at (425) 348-xxxx to verify that we have your lost item.</p>
    </div>


    <script>
        var coll = document.getElementsByClassName("collapsible");
        var i;

        for (i = 0; i < coll.length; i++) {
            coll[i].addEventListener("click", function () {
                this.classList.toggle("active");
                var content = this.nextElementSibling;
                if (content.style.display === "block") {
                    content.style.display = "none";
                } else {
                    content.style.display = "block";
                }
            });
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>

